Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Fearing and Loving: Making Sense of the Warrior
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0b88hl4
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 7 Jul 2018
Historian Margaret MacMillan asks why both men and women go to war. "We are both fascinated and repulsed by war and those who fight," she says. In this lecture, recorded at York University, she explores looks at the role of the warrior in history and culture and analyses how warriors are produced. And she interrogates the differences that gender plays in war. Anita Anand presents the programme recorded in front of an audience, including a question and answer session. Producer: Jim Frank Editor: Hugh Levinson. Show less